  "texts": [
    "The ability to diagnose the performance of pollsters keeps the industry honest and the public well-informed.",
    "Such diagnostics are traditionally possible due to the relatively simple dimensions of the polling problem, which traditionally boils down to a few simple heuristics: (a) to what extent was turnout taken into account, and how?",
    "; (b) to what extent were the samples used appropriately statistically powered and representative?",
    "; (c) was there evidence for 'late swings', 'shy voters', 'differential non-response', or other miscellaneous phenomena that could plausibly have contributed to a polling failure?",
    "Comparable properties are not always available for artificially intelligent polling."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "; (b) to what extent were the samples used appropriately statistically powered and representative?"
  ]
}